By Rita Iliya Minna â€“ The Secretary to the Government of Niger State, Alhaji Ahmed Matane, on Wednesday tasked the Nigerian Air Force (NAF) to continue to safeguard the territorial integrity of the nation. He gave the charge when he received NAF officers of Niger State extraction who graduated from the Basic Military Training Course at the Nigerian Air Force Military Training Centre, Kaduna. Matane urged them to contribute their quota to the fight against insurgency, banditry, kidnapping and other related crimes bedeviling the country. He called on the officers to always embrace the core value of integrity, service before self and excellence which are essential ingredients of high reputations. He then charged the airmen and airwoman to be resilient and courageous in the performance of their duties. (NAN)